    "(95)Here, the TD target estimate only looks one step ahead-and is therefore referred to as TD(0).",
    "The generalization is called TD(N).",
    "In the limit N → ∞, the method is equivalent to Monte Carlo learning, where all steps are performed and a true target is obtained.",
    "Deep Q-learning introduces a NN for the action-value function Q(s, a; θ).",
    "Its quality is assessed with a loss composed of the mean squared error of the TD error.C = E 1 2 r t + γ max a Q(s t+1, a; θ) -Q(s t, a t; θ) 2(96)Lastly, the optimal policy π(s) maximizing the actionvalue function Q(s, a; θ) is extracted:π(s) = arg max a Q(s, a; θ) (97)Fig. 22Fig."
